Comment 2: 
I've managed to capture the _go_.6 (and the rest or the $WORK dir) for the following
results:
* Success
* pack: non-object file
* pack: bad package import section 

They all appear exactly the same.
I've uploaded it to http://slu.is/go/non-object-file/_go_.zip should it be of use.

I have tried reproducing the problem on a clean VM and have been unable to do so.
I have completely removed go from the affected machine and re-installed it and the error
remains. 'Go env' is the same on both machines, the $GOROOT tree is exactly the same
between machines.

It seems environmental, but I don't know of any other difference between machines that
could lead to this.
